review_blob: Great pilsener, beautiful golden color, great taste like barley when is cold close to the freezing point.
Beautiful color with just a hint of pumpkin, taste more like tea leaves te bitterness strong. Not my favorite but a good ale overall.

If you looking for a pumpkin flavored beer not the best choice. This ale is not pumpkin spicy as supposed to be. Smells like cooked wheat. Good ale but not my favorite. Very diluted only 4.5 % alcohol.
Amazing hazel color smells like malt, little bitterness in the palate good apearance.
This ale has a Caramel color, tasted like herbs, not bad clove and pumpkin spiced accentuated good overall.
Hazey caramel color, spice and cloves flavor, not lot of pumpkin pie flavor. Good with chips :)
beer_name: Buffalo Bills Americas Original Pumpkin Ale
